			<h2>Evidence behind The Power Of Play</h2>
			<ul class="clearfix">
				<li>
					<p>There is a growing body of research that shows a link between play and the development of cognitive and social skills that are prerequisites for learning more complex concepts as children get older. For example, play is linked to growth in memory, self-regulation, oral language, and recognizing symbols. It has been linked to higher levels of school adjustment and increased social development. </p>
					<a class="button c-2-a" target="_blank" href="http://www.scholastic.com/teachers/article/why-children-need-play-0">Read the Article</a>
				</li>
				<li>
					<p>Young children today need advocates. They need adults who want to preserve and protect the conditions that they will flourish in. </p>
